enge_integration_qualitygpu/videos\r\n  video_names_file: /home/ddbb/comma_video_compression_challenge_integration_qualitygpu/public_test_video_names.txt\r\n=== Evaluation results over 600 samples ===\r\n  Average PoseNet Distortion: 0.00048759\r\n  Average SegNet Distortion: 0.00077435\r\n  Submission file size: 57,329 bytes\r\n  Original uncompressed size: 37,545,489 bytes\r\n  Compression Rate: 0.00152692\r\n  Final score: 100*segnet_dist + √(10*posenet_dist) + 25*rate = 0.19\r\n```\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1500\" height=\"900\" alt=\"maskzero_metric_four_panel\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/82f6569f-e487-4b34-a6b9-4786e43c4f62\" />\r\n\r\n# does your submission require gpu for evaluation (inflation)?\r\nyes\r\n\r\n# did you include the compression script? and want it to be merged?\r\nno compression script, but did want it merged if it is a valid approach\r\n\r\n# additional comments\r\nI vibe coded too close to the Sun. I thought I worked with Codex to create an innovative solution building off the Quantizr mask approach, but then I saw https://github.com/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/pull/68 and realized I had just been moving bytes from the archive into my inflate.py. I was working on a write up of various solutions submitted to the competition, and why I thought mine was unique, but now I feel like this only contributes an exploit.\r\n\r\nI'll consider finishing the writeup this weekend since I still think it's a cool competition and the solutions so far have all been very cool.","created_at":"2026-05-01T08:26:12Z","updated_at":"2026-05-03T17:36:23Z","closed_at":null,"merged_at":null,"merge_commit_sha":"2e885c99a0c150b31218f72326777960297451b7","assignees":[],"requested_reviewers":[{"login":"YassineYousfi","id":29985433,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5OTg1NDMz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/29985433?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/YassineYousfi","html_url":"https://github.com/YassineYousfi","